@page "/cultures"
@rendermode InteractiveServer
@inherits PageBase

<h1>Cultures — overview</h1>

<p>
    The host wires <code>ICultureProvider</code> (read) and <code>ICultureManager</code>
    (write). Both are <strong>scoped</strong>; mutations fire <code>OnChange</code> which
    propagates to providers, layouts and pages.
</p>

<p class="muted">
    Inside this Razor file we use <code>@@inherits PageBase</code> instead of <code>@@inject</code>
    so that the page automatically gets <code>Culture</code>, <code>Workspace</code>,
    <code>Catalog</code>, <code>Authenticated</code>, <code>Toast</code>, <code>Cookie</code>
    and <code>BreadcrumbsProvider</code> as protected properties — straight from
    <code>ExtensionsBase</code>.
</p>

<section class="card">
    <h2>Quick switcher</h2>
    <p>Current culture: <strong>@Culture.Current.Value</strong></p>
    <select @onchange="OnCultureChanged" value="@Culture.Current.Value">
        @foreach (var lang in CultureManager.Supported)
        {
            <option value="@lang.Code">@lang.NativeName (@lang.Code)</option>
        }
    </select>
    <p class="muted">
        Switching here is reflected globally — the layout's switcher and any page subscribed
        to <code>Culture.OnChange</code> re-render.
    </p>
</section>

<section class="card">
    <h2>Inline translation</h2>
    <p>The two helpers are equivalent:</p>
    <pre>Culture.Translate("Welcome").Value
Translated t = Culture.Translate("Hello {0}!", "world");  // implicit-string</pre>
    <ul>
        <li>Translate: <strong>@Culture.Translate("Welcome").Value</strong></li>
        <li>With args: <strong>@Culture.Translate("Hello {0}!", "world").Value</strong></li>
    </ul>
    <p class="muted">
        No translations registered — the missing-key tracker stores the request and the
        provider returns the input verbatim. A real host wires
        <code>ITranslationRepository</code> with a real source.
    </p>
</section>

@code {
    [Inject] ICultureManager CultureManager { get; set; } = default!;

    // PageBase already subscribes Culture.OnChange → StateHasChanged and disposes itself.

    void OnCultureChanged(ChangeEventArgs e)
    {
        if (e.Value is string code)
            CultureManager.SetCulture(code);
    }
}
